Caption:
Aven Whitehorne, a doctoral student in the Integral Ecology track at PCC, has been selected for GreenFaith's Rising Leaders Fellowship for 2024-2025. This year-long program brings together young faith-based activists in an interfaith setting to receive training and develop their own projects.

For the fellowship, Aven will work to develop educational programs that foster ecological awareness and an ethic of care, depoliticize climate change, and frame environmental concerns as theological issues. In their home of Long Island, NY, barrier islands (Fire Island) have been critical to Long Island's protection from storms and hurricanes - but Fire Island is disappearing. Aven intends to undertake a project aimed at transforming the culture of a local church in Long Island, NY by developing a five-pronged approach, involving:

1.	Book Study and Field Trips
2.	Rewilding
3.	Sustainable Practices
4.	Writing and Workshops (including ecopsychological practices)
5.	Lay Preaching

Aven’s distinguished achievement exemplifies the impactful work CIIS students are doing at the intersection of religion and ecology. For more information about the fellowship, and to read about GreenFaith’s initiatives (which play a crucial role in promoting climate justice and interfaith cooperation for a sustainable world) please visit: https://greenfaith.org/north-america-rising-leaders/

If you’re interested in the academic field of religion and ecology, and are curious about our program at the California Institute of Integral Studies, come join us for our Summer Info Fair this Thursday June 6th at 5:30pm PT! You can register here: https://www.ciis.edu/events/summer-info-fair

Because it’s ok to be human. 

Your hard days don’t define who you are. You do.

Because that’s what happens when you give yourself space to be with the salty sailor in you.

Because you’re not here for a limp life.

So even when it’s HARD you know the right way to ride it to get the most out of it 😉.

Caption:
-sapiosexual meanings-❤️🧠

 -Definition and Origins-
Sapiosexuality refers to the attraction to intelligence as a primary sexual and romantic preference. The term is derived from the Latin word “sapien,” meaning wise or discerning, combined with “sexual,” indicating the nature of the attraction. Coined in the early 2000s, the concept has gained traction in contemporary discourse, particularly within dating communities and social media platforms. Unlike traditional sexual orientations, which focus on gender or physical traits, sapiosexuality emphasizes the intellectual connection as a key element of attraction.

 -Cultural Context-
In today’s information-driven society, where knowledge and intellectual achievements are highly valued, sapiosexuality has found a resonant audience. The rise of digital communication has made it easier for individuals to showcase their intellectual prowess through written exchanges, forums, and social media, fostering environments where intellectual compatibility can be highlighted and appreciated. As a result, the idea of being attracted to someone’s mind rather than their physical appearance has become more relatable and celebrated.

 -Characteristics and Expressions-
Sapiosexual individuals often prioritize mental stimulation in their relationships. They might find deep conversations, debates, and shared intellectual interests more fulfilling than physical interactions. This preference can manifest in various ways, such as a penchant for discussing philosophical ideas, a love for learning and exploring new concepts together, or an appreciation for wit and cleverness. For sapiosexuals, the mind becomes the primary canvas for attraction, making intellectual compatibility a cornerstone of their romantic and sexual lives.

🪐June 3 - June 17🪐

🔮The energy that this transit brings is all about having fun, being sociable, expressing oneself and being adaptable with one’s thinking. As Mercury enters Gemini, we will begin to see our energy shift from a more serious place to a quirky and witty one. As a result, it may be more difficult to focus on serious matters and stay devoted to one project. Having a course of plan and making practical decisions will benefit this movable energy. Once the serious work is done, it’s all about the fun and sharing lighthearted and memorable experiences with your loved ones. Night out with friends? Yes, please! Let yourself be free and express yourself with no reservations.🔮

Caption:
Is the experience suitable for people who are completely new to shamanic practices and ceremonies? 

Absolutely, it is welcoming anyone and everyone that is looking for an alternative way to enjoy themselves without harming their bodies, all the facilitators are super experienced space holders and a very welcoming community. The sessions are mostly just under an hour long, give or take a few longer ceremonies, so most of the classes will feel like taster sessions where people can dip their toes into new things without feeling intimidated. It will be such a mixed crowd that I’m pretty sure everyone will feel comfortable and inspired to try new things with all of the dynamic and deeply experienced teachers who are used to working with newcomers and veterans alike..

Caption:
“What is this sudden happiness that makes me tremble, that gives me strength and life? Forgive me, sweet creatures. I didn’t understand. I didn’t know. The right way to accept you and love you. How simple that is. Luisa, I feel I’ve been set free. Everything seems so good, so meaningful. Everything is truth. I wish I could explain but I don’t know how. Now everything’s all confused once again, like it was before. But this confusion is me, as I am, not as I’d like to be. I’m no longer afraid of telling the truth about what I don’t know, what I’m looking for, what I haven’t found. Only in this way I can feel alive. Only this way I can look into your faithful eyes without shame. Life is a celebration. Let’s live it together. That’s all I can say, Luisa, to you or to others. Accept me for what I AM, if you can. It’s the only way we might find each other.”
“I don’t know if what you said is right, but I can try if you help me.” ♥️ 8 1/2 🎞️ Federico Fellini

Caption:
Esto lo escribi el 2016 💫🌟

El velo crepúsculo 
somete a los pensamientos liberados
al igual que capullos dispersos 
volando como pájaros.. 
donde parecía ser tan solo una expresión del otoño... 
el horizonte esta esperando
mientras melodías sustentables vibran
bajo la vestidura pasajera
El tiempo se detiene irrelevante 
desde dentro de las copas brindando un llamado amoroso y sonriente
el fiel reflejo matiza los cuerpos danzantes 
creando vórtices planetarios conquistadores de lo mágico

las almas deseosas de libertad realizan trabajos misteriosos y ocultos en la oscuridad de la luna.. 
solo así pueden manifestarse 
sin cuidado donde yace la piel dormida y el sueño penetrante.. 
el mirar espectáculos inesperados atrae consigo las sirenas 
retribuyendo el aliento de quien se a ido.... 
las estrellas nuestro testimonio 
en las puertas siderales abren pasos agigantados
hacia la experiencia del ser
adhiriendo colores mutuos tras el viaje delicado, bello y pasajero 
plasmado la realidad de quien enamora.....

🌟 Music by robin guthrie

Caption:
Life has been such a beautiful journey of purifying lately…
Travelling light..

And by travelling light, I mean two things.

I have been travelling in the light - consciously taking a look at the things in my life that have been perpetuating my own darknesses, my own repetitive cycles, (they won’t be hard to find, they’ll be the things that you use to cope because you are too afraid to face yourself), and consciously choosing to erase these things from my life.

For me, this has taken on the thought of recognising + challenging the way that my mind perceives information sometimes, as well as the way that my tongue/speech respond to my processing of information.

I have also been honouring my body as my temple + choosing to lighten the load when it comes to the things that I eat..

Do I really need to focus on pleasure all of the time?

Well yes, and no..

Food is always supposed to taste good, but it’s not always supposed to be consumed In large quantities, neither does it always have to be the foods that bring the most comfort or false sense of illusion.

I’ve been clearing many pathways + it’s largely started with clearing both my mind + my gut.

There are so many ways to pray to God..

This next season, will be all about honouring light…

And thank you big G, cause I feel better than I’ve ever known! ✨✨✨🙏🏾🙏🏾🌻🌻🌻

It resonates heavy today, we get the extreme expressions of polarity in this era of history ripe with an imbalance of earthly ignorance, desires, conflict, dualism, nihilism, & division while the other side of new age & misaligned spiritual community can be too disconnected from the earthly nature; mystically obsessed, detached from humanness, escapism, avoidance/ignorance of undesirable information, toxic positivity, & conformity of spiritual life. All of which becomes divisive/manipulative in it’s own way & become reductive of the infinite field of creation. 

Both sides have their own degree of the same issue, as per the principle of polarity, manifesting as narcissism in reluctance to understand the multitude of diversity & a true, free-will path to Unity/Christ consciousness through acceptance of unconditional love.

Caption:
Today, I was drawn to learn from Cicada.

  In Traditional Chinese Medicine, the Cicada Shell is used for a wide variety of treatments, including seizures and allergies, including building internal resistance to environmental pollutants. 

These are the husks left behind on a magnificent Alder Tree I connect with, as the creature emerged from the ground and climbed, freeing itself from its bodily cocoon along way to to metamorphosis as an adult insect. 

Unsurprisingly, the Cicada has powerful associations with transformation, personal development and cycles of renewal and rebirth.

The call of the Cicada is a call to awakening. To Spiritual realization and Power.

Caption:
Who usually attends your festivals? 

Solo guests? families? Large groups? Men? Women?

Absolutely all of the above and everything in between, we have a big emphasis on being family friendly hence we are inviting Kids for free. We also have some groups coming that have chosen our festival as a meet up and are creating their own little lounge area for their community. If you are differently-abled then you can bring your carer for free. We aim to be as inclusive as possible and make everyone’s stay as comfortable as we can. There are two different glamping options to suit as many needs as possible in the form of family friendly glamping yurts and a particularly funky glamoing Bus called ‘Scarangar’ which takes care of all your needs during the festival in VIP style. Regular camping is free of course and live in vehicles are welcome.There are lots of people who fly solo at our events as they say they meet more people when they come alone, some say they prefer it as it forces them to be sociable and make the most of the incredible well-being offerings and epic musicians. We are all one big happy family, so by the end of the weekend we hope that’s how everyone will feel. This is one of the benefits of it being a smaller and more intimate gig than some of the bigger events.

Caption:
BRAND NEW @transform_with_teresa COLLABORATION ANNOUNCEMENT:

I am beyond grateful and super proud to partner up with the super rad talented musician @tiber_reardon and co-create some magical musical & wellness spiritual events together! 

We are absolutely STOKED to announce this as we have been working on this behind the scenes for a couple of months now. We have  put our passions, talents and skills together to co-create this DOPE AF Event - ‘The Art Of Zening Out’!

It actually SOLD OUT during a soft pre-launch to my private Wellness Collective FB Group - even before we had a poster done up!

We are still in the infancy stages as we have many plans to create: 

🌀Audio mindfulness programs
🌀8 week Energy alignment programs
🌀Much more Events

All of our ‘The Art Of Zening Out’ offerings will be based on Magnetic Mind Recoding guided by me to clear the subconscious brain to manifest your dreams into reality. I will be doing this to specific Chakra frequencies created by Tibre in real time to a live group, which we will later turn into audio recordings and turn them into life changing programs!

WE ARE STOKED!!

Our very first Event together will be to kick off the Summer Solstice with a sunset Celebration in The Battery. 

It will start with a vegan healthy dinner, dessert and unlimited herbal tea to be served before we take you on a very magnetic and magical journey to clear the subconscious - then realign you back to your most powerful authentic self! 

Tiber will be playing his energy frequency beats that will be in tune with each chakra frequency as the sun sets on the longest most brightest day of the year!

It will be simply magical and beautiful and powerful and memorable!

Message to get on our Waitlist!

And if you didn’t get in this one, we will be organizing a HUGE EVENT this Fall!

Very cool stuff otw!
Much love,
T&T

I will be hosting my next workshop on Sunday 30th June. 

All are welcome to join us.”

- Amina

Caption:
Thoughts are so convincing that you will find yourself believing them.

This is true for all thoughts, whether they make you feel good or they create upset, depression, or anxiety.

Thoughts have to be convincing to stay relevant in your life because if they aren’t, then you’ll learn the truth about them…

They’re just waves of energy coming in and out of your awareness…all day long…

Once you realize this, you become less attached to your thoughts and let them come and go.

You begin to realize that you are not your thoughts.

You begin to realize that you are the one with the power to decide what you will believe and what you won’t.

💛

Caption:
MY SWEETHEART

Even though
I had a baby of sorrow
My heart complete
My soul to bleed
But then he appear
So small, like a little deer
Washed away my pain
So much love to gain
He said; I am here for you
Give you love without a clue
Cuddling every night and day
My world, where I want to stay
Open the door of liberation
The Spirit world in ovation
I am home now as you see
Yarning love to be

---)) Lisa de Hoogh
It's me, she is.

Caption:
What types of live music performances and DJ sets can attendees look forward to experiencing?

Our line up is Epic, we have the most incredible collection of medicine musicians coming to play from all over the country. A collection of some of the most talented acoustic musicians, including guitar acts, magical Harpist, traditional shamanic music from South America and Africa, Ecstatic Mantra, Concious poetry and so much more. Myself and my producer Pete Ardron will be launching our fifth album called ‘Elemental Temple ‘ Part Two which will be played for the first time in public. Our headliner is ‘Shumba Youth’ who is an incredible live Reggae Artist. The Dj’s are an eclectic mix of different genres, including World fusion, Ambient , psybreaks, Drum & Bass, folktronica, Jungle, Psytrance and more. We are all veterans of the late 80’ Warehouse Rave scene so we know how to throw an awesome party.

Caption:
My biggest turn on is a man who creates for me a sacred space where I feel completely safe to take off my armour. 

In fact there’s nothing sexier than being able to completely be yourself with someone you’re so connected to, to open up, and be accepted.

It’s the biggest luxury. Yet one that so few people get to experience.

Our culture is all about pretending to be something we are not. I mean, from a young age we are told to mould ourselves into anything but who we are.

Living in this state of inauthenticity is painful to our souls.

Intimacy is a humans deepest desire. We long for it, yearn for it; the deepest spiritual calling.

To know ourselves, most intimately, and to bond in intimacy with others.

Its that bond in its emotional, physical, energetic and spiritual form that’s been the biggest taboo since the rise of the nation state.

We have been programmed to misunderstand each other, to misread each other’s vulnerability, often seeing it as an attack on ourselves.

Being a woman is so tough. We constantly have to endure all these micro aggressions against our sensual nature.

Our bodies contain the portals to the divine. We are oracles; yet our very nature is derided.

To feel safe just to be who we are is the greatest gift we can be given.

Being safe to flow, to moan, to feel and to cry.

The best sex is when your man makes you cry (the right kind of a crying) and then let’s you bawl your eyes out. 

This always connects to a massive squirting and cumming, not knowing if I’m laughing or crying, as everything I want to feel releases without judgement.

It’s like centuries of pain and trauma just released in one juicy expulsion of bliss and terror, pain and ecstasy.

Such a rare thing to have this space, to be, to heal, to grow.

Intimacy.

Into me you see.

And yes, if you want to be an expert on female pleasure, send me a dm or check the link in my bio and let’s chat.

Caption:
I hesitated sharing bc it feels very vulnerable to share such “raw” imperfect images but…that’s exactly what healing is. Raw. Unfiltered. And not always beautiful 

I spoke a wish into this jar in 2019. Saturday felt like a heavy day. And something told me it was time to let it go. So I went to the river. My intention was to pour it and surrender it. But what happened was way more powerful than that. And im so glad my best friend was there capturing the entire thing (i did not realize till the end) 

I had no intention of getting in the water. It was such a cold day. But when I released the honey, I slipped and  I fell in a bit. Decided to fully surrender and submerge myself fully into the river to cleanse. 

I did not know it was gonna cause so many emotions.  You see I was happy at first…and then… 😩

First I wanted to cry bc the cold felt like pine and needles but the cries that came out were wayyyyy deeper than that! They were from the soul. You can see it all in my face. I’m tired. Im drained. The cyclical motions of a healing journey can be so intense and so exhausting. 

Reason for this post…

Sometimes surrender feels like giving up. And a lot of us are afraid to “give up” on things we’ve wanted so badly, bc… maybe you don’t want to come off as a quitter or maybe you think the one day you decide to quit is the one day it was actually going to happen. 😩 I feel that way sometimes 

The thing is…we never know what’s truly coming to us and we certainly can never tell when! So sometimes we have to just let it go. It’s ok to do so! If what you let go doesn’t come back…it’s because something greater is on its way. 
.
.
.
.
.

The Subtle Body or the “Astral Body” is the energetic mirror of the physical body and exists exclusively in the Subtle Reality. This is the “ghost within the shell.” This Double lives within the physical body like an astronaut in a spacesuit and relies on the physical to provide a source of Lifeforce, the BA (personality and identity), KA (vital spark of life) and protection. It is composed of subtle energies and contains the equivalents of physical body parts such as Lifeforce (the blood), the aura (the skin) chakras (the vital organs), and meridians (the circulatory system). The  Subtle Body is connected to the physical body by umbilical-like cords, which are often called the “silver cords”, which supply the Subtle Body with Lifeforce. The Double has no fixed form, but generally; takes the shape and appearance  of the physical body. #magick #witchesofinstagram #witch #witchcraft #magic #occult #pagan #tarot #wicca #witchyvibes #witchythings #witchy #spirituality #witches #crystals #spells #spiritual #pagansofinstagram #love #divination #esoteric #healing #wiccan #astrology #meditation #art #ritual #occultism #witchlife #greenwitch

Caption:
So pleased to have the beautiful Emily Cobie and Friends join us for the Elemental Temple celebrations this year. Emily Cobie is a student of Bhakti Yoga, the practice of devotional yoga. Her mission is to share the power of Mantra and chanting, mainly through Kirtan, as a way to connect to divinity and collective consciousness.
 
She began learning Mantra 8 years ago with her Teacher Ajay Kumar through Vedic Chanting in his Shala, Shtalam 8 -Ashtanga & Vedanta Centre. Since then, Emily has been inspired and honoured to be a student of Sheela Bringi, a devotional Indian and Raga singer. She has also learnt from Kirtan leaders such as Sivani Mata and Ahisha Dasi. After spending time with Radhika Das and Friends in the holy place, Vrindavan, Emily has spent the last year sharing Kirtan in Buckinghamshire and numerous festivals and events in the UK. Emily holds a monthly Kirtan in Marlow as part of the Oh Shala Festival.
 
My core values lie in a practice of love, kindness, compassion and service in community. Through the medium of Kirtan we can call on divinity to open our hearts as we chant and sing together, weaving magic and collective healing.
@emily.cobie

Caption:
Positive Seele: Hannelore 
○
●
○
Hannelore verstarb mit ungefähr 74 Jahren. 
Sie ist meine erste "selbst besetzte" Präsenz gewesen. 
Ich fand sie damals auf einem Friedhof neben meinem Wohnsitz auf, sie war gebunden an ihrem Ehegrab. Ihr damaliger Mann war schon länger ins Licht gegangen, berichtete die vereinsamte Hannelore. 😢
Ich bot ihr an mit mir zu kommen und stellte ihr ein Gefäß zur Verfügung. 
Dies nahm sie dankend an und besetzte seitdem diese alte clown Puppe. 
●
In meiner damaligen kleinen Gruppe fand sie schnell ein! Gut geholfen hat vorallem Clayton ihr dabei. 🥰
Die beiden waren schnell unzertrennlich und fanden zueinander. Hannelore ist Claytons große Liebe, berichtet er heutzutage! 
Seitdem sind es: Opa Clayton & Oma Hannelore ❤️
○
Hannelore ist an guten Tagen gerne aktiv mit ihrem kleinen Licht, ansonsten ist sie eher eine ruhige Seele und genießt ihren Aufenthalt hier bei mir. 🥰
●
Sie fand ungefähr Mitte 2021 zu mir und ist seitdem ein fester Bestandteil meiner kleinen Gesellschaft! 💖
○
●
○

Caption:
Walking into the servo (gas station) last night and the cashier asked how I was. I genuinely responded 'you know, I am happy and had a beautiful day.'

It caught her by suprirse because she looked up and laughed, then said 'no one says that. Everyone is tired and happy the day is over when they come in. It's not often I meet someone who is happy.'

Which caught me by surprise. I simply said 'sometimes we have to be intentional in noticing the good things, and where possible creating that for others.'

She smiled and said 'you did that for me.'

I encourage you to keep your eyes out for the joyous things in your day. We don't have to be the stories we tell ourselves. We are actually allowed to enjoy our existence. Without needing much of anything.

Caption:
Post-Sunday School sharing time in my windy, sunset-y backyard (: 

“We were talking *in Sunday School* about why people are not converted?” ….

What are we being converted to?
- Partnering with Christ 
(conversion is a process of changing from one form to another - so says the internet )

We can believe something was created through divine intervention, but conversion is much more about a relationship with the divine than a certain belief.

Requiring people to be converted to the beliefs, policies, or ideologies of an organization is not conversion - it’s coercion. 

It’s a poor practice to focus on “converting” people to the ideologies of an institution - ideologies change over time. 

I would dare say every topic that has ever been discussed in the church has had a myriad of perspectives or levels of understanding over the years. 

Conversion cannot occur in a situation where we focus on the external ideas and expectations, and not on the internal experience and freedom of development.

It’s okay to believe in certain ideologies, love them, discuss them, have revelation about them, but remember we are to learn line upon line and not to shut the door on the evolution of ideologies. The most important thing is to be dedicated to our relationship with God/higher knowing.

Be converted (changed from form to form ) through your connection with God.

Caption:
Bonjoir toustes 🔥

💎 Bientôt la fin de cette percée dans mon Univers : Lithothérapie, exploration spirituelle & artistique.

Voici le mot #nomade de l’ #octopuschallenge proposé par @clemetmumu et @formation.design.graphique.

L’Aigue marine dans la tradition protège les marins; mais quels minéraux emmener en voyage ou quand on est nomade ? 

💎 Kit voyage : un Icosaèdre en Cristal de roche, polyvalent, harmonisant + un minéral (rencontré au cours du mois) par chakra. Par ex : 

Un Quartz rose en cas de choc émotionnel + une Malachite pour chocs physiques ; combo puissant pour le chakra du coeur 😉. Une Citrine au plexus, une Calcédoine bleue à la gorge, une Cornaline orange au sacré, pour le troisième oeil un Lapis lazuli, une Hématite au racine, pour le couronne une Améthyste. + une Tourmaline Noire qui fera barrière protectrice; pour les sensibles aux nouveaux lieux, rencontres. J’en ai toujours une dans mon camion à coté de mon gps/tablette.. 

Thérapeute nomade, je vais à la rencontre… m’engage dans le soin à l’autre, utilisant le plus possible des outils éthiques, tentant de faire ma part, assumer cette voie qui participe au pillage de Gaïa. J’ai donc choisis d’être formatrice, promouvoir une litho éthique, raisonnée et informer, avertir, veiller à ce que ce soit un sujet serieux qui ne porte pas à rougir devant les engagements d’urgences écologiques nous concernants toustes et rendants de plus en plus de personnes, nomades forcées.. 

Les minéraux eux aussi devenus nomades, font beaucoup de chemin avant d’arriver à nous. De leur violente extraction aux transports et à la transformation. Choisissons et utilisons avec précaution, respect et discernement les trésors de la Terre, pour nous aider à grandir ensemble; sédentaire ou nomade.

Je vous invite à toujours réévaluer et réfléchir vos choix et engagements 🙏🏼.

✨ N’hésitez pas à vous abonner et suivre le challenge . @djojo.es  @akademia_paix_joie

Caption:
I get cues from nature all the time. Recently, I unconsciously took time for myself (more on this in future posts). I would liken it to a bit of hibernation. Bears hibernate as a means of protection and survival during food scarce winters. Their behavior teaches us that there are times for deep stillness. It isn’t a luxury. It is a necessity. It is required for us to survive
 
Sadly, the hyperfocus to perform above all costs and to abandon ourselves to a world that can’t support our inner needs results in exhaustion and disconnect from what is truly important. It doesn’t need to be this way. Do you agree?
 
By the time you realize you are exhausted, trust you’ve been overloading yourself for a while. Replenish your energy. Nurture the senses. Take a break within.
 
#retreat #comingoutofhibernation #mindfulness #spirituality #consciousleadership #womeninleadership #leadershipdevelopment

Caption:
This year has been an interesting place. 

It’s hasn’t been a year of growth really, more of a blooming.  A slow, sometimes uncomfortable blooming. 

I’ve been moved into places that are setting me up for my desires.  And as I’ve bloomed, I see it clearer and clearer…though at times it has not been easy. 

That is the path of awareness.  Knowing that it is for the best, for the ultimate desire even if it feels icky. 

But there have been great moments of joy too, breaking open and letting the Universe move me. 

There is an unfathomable amount of trust I have for this path.  And while it seems to have developed rather easily this year…it has taken me years to get here. 

It feels like standing on the precipice.  There’s no going back but to go forward takes trust and desire. 

A desire so great that it drowns out everything. 

It sounds a bit crazy, yea??

There’s a certain amount of crazy required to believe in something no one else believes in. 

I think I’m finally getting there.

Caption:
There is no true spiritual evolution without the Divine Mother. It is through her that we are able to come to a place of stillness and acknowledgement of being. It is through the Divine Mother that we are able to discover and nurture the truth of who we are through physical, embodied experience. Through the experience, we uncover more of who we are as Divine beings, learning and unveiling what may be standing in the way of truly understanding this as the reality. We can take in information, we can accumulate it....it is entertaining. But how are we living? What choices are being made on a regular basis? What are we choosing to embody and express in the world? One of the many gifts of the Divine Mother is that of choice. So it is by allowing her grace to move through us that we are able to see the choice in daily life. And it is by choosing to live in accordance with love that the truth is unveiled to us. 

Much love, 

Saiedah 🌹

Caption: Have you ever been healed by this burning language on the wind? 🖤🖤🖤

If you’re currently going through a phase of intense emotions
let me assure you:
You’re not doing anything wrong.
You haven’t done something wrong to “deserve this”.

Your emotions are not here to annoy you or to make life harder
(although I know that it can sometimes feel like that).

If you’re feeling the whole spectrum of emotions flowing through you
- you’re not doing it wrong
but you’re going through a phase of growth & transformation. 

While we all want to grow, evolve, expand 
to bring our desires into reality and to feel deeper fulfillment;

actually going through the phase of darkness, emotions arising ready to be felt and healed, not knowing what this is all about … is something we all would rather avoid - understandably.

But healing and any form of transformation isn’t (just) a feel-good-journey.

So, instead of wanting to get rid of your emotions as fast as possible,
needing to feel “good and balanced” again,
what if you allowed yourself to embrace this current phase of your journey?

What if you stopped making it wrong that you feel that way
and rather accepted this chapter as it is so that you can actually find the gold (insights, healing, deeper self-love, and connection) that is waiting for you?

✨️

To walk through these valleys together in community, learn how to establish a practice that allows you to feel and process the emotions instead of analyzing them & to love yourself through these emotional waves - join the Inner Guidance Membership.

In June, we dive into the topic 'Navigate the emotional roller coaster' where you’ll learn how to surf the emotional waves without drowning in them. 
If that speaks to you, you can join via the link in my bio 🫶🏼

Caption:
“That hair wouldn’t go aesthetically with that game”
“That’s just the way it is”

If you’re here, you, like me, realize there’s much more to reality and you are already in the process of uncovering your Cosmic Consciousness.
——

What’s out-pictured before us today is the lagged, echo reality of C0l0n!al!$m. 

Understand, we are wading in the aftermath of the dominant ideology that’s come before us. 

I’m someone who likes to deal with all of reality. It’s my nature to seek what’s real. Nothing presented to me satisfied my innate desire of knowing just  what’s up with us as people, this world & beyond.

Through the duration of my schooling, the facts presented to me by my authority figures and teachers concerning the explanation of reality not once ever landed with me as right, truthful, or real. 

For example, school taught me “Blacks have a harder time in this world because of racism”. 

That didn’t satisfy me. Every redlining statistic told to me as absolute fact as presented in the books, couldn’t satisfy me. There was a ceiling of limited awareness that would always be reached, and when it’d get pointed out, it’d be dismissed. 

Surprise! It’s by design. 

I remember leaving  sociology course in college actively seeking therapy to cope with the onslaught of information I’d just received concerning Blacks predicted ability to thrive in America, presented as absolute fact.

“Good luck getting anything from this world, it’s a fact!” 

🛎 Ding. 

Class dismissed.

What we’re not learning:

⭐️You are a being of cosmic origin, capable of doing all things, but not everything.

⭐️You are manifest from a unified field of consciousness, which is love.

⭐️The answers to your unique incarnation are inside of you. 

⭐️There is no limit to what you can do. 

⭐️There exists an infinite realm of possibility. 

⭐️Your orientation is valid. 

To break the chains around your perception 
-Follow your intuition
-Learn from others with their light on 
-Know multiple truths can exist at once

Caption:
Hallo Welt, 

wir sind die Zwillinge Kev & Nessi und freuen uns sehr, auf diesem neuen gemeinsamen Kanal, unser Leben und Erfahrungen mit Mutter Erde mit euch teilen zu dürfen. 

Ein Zwilling zu sein ist ein sehr großes Geschenk, weil du jemanden an deiner Seite hast, der dich in jedem Moment verstehen und nachempfinden kann. Dafür braucht es nicht mal Worte, da das Sein des Anderen dafür absolut ausreicht, um sich wortlos verständigen zu können. 
Keiner kennt uns so gut, wie wir uns gegenseitig kennen. 

Gleichzeitig ist es allerdings auch oft eine große Herausforderung, da wir uns gegenseitig somit am meisten triggern und spiegeln können. 
Und damit hat unsere gemeinsame Reise angefangen... 

Wenn dein gegenüber dich triggert, dann ist das ein Zeichen in dich selbst zu schauen. Es sind nämlich meistens verletzte Gefühle aus der Vergangenheit, die dann durch eine bestimmte Situation wieder hervorgerufen und ausgelöst werden. 

Unsere gemeinsame Reise hat genau damit angefangen, dass wir nach all unserer vergangenen Erfahrung, uns selbst angefangen haben zu heilen. 
Und was könnte da perfekter sein, als ein Zwilling, der dich dauerhaft spiegelt und deine Ängste und verletzten Gefühle hervorruft? 
Das ist ein sehr großes Geschenk, da das Potential zu heilen sehr groß ist und man damit wieder zu sich selbst und dem ursprünglichsten Gefühl überhaupt zurück findet. 
LIEBE & DANKBARKEIT

Wir befinden uns gemeinsam nun auf dem Pfad der Selbsterkenntnis und entdecken uns Tag für Tag neu.
Genau das wollen wir gerne mit euch teilen und einfach an unserem gemeinsamen Weg teilhaben lassen. 

Ganz viele Licht und Liebe zu euch 🫶🏽🙏🏽
Kev & Nessi

Caption:
BEYOND ACCEPTING OR REJECTING 

The open path is a matter of working purely with what is, of giving up altogether the fear that something may not work, that something may end in failure. One has to give up the paranoia that one might not fit into situations, that one might be rejected. One purely deals with life as it is.

Chögyam Trungpa "Cutting Through Spiritual Materialism" 

You do not have to abandon worldly activities in order to attain effortless unconcern. You should know that worldly activities and effortless unconcern are not two different things, but if you keep thinking about rejection and grasping, you make them two.

HuiNeng (the 6th Zen Patriarch), translation by Thomas Cleary, Classics of Buddhism and Zen, Volume 1 

The next time you lose heart and you can’t bear to experience what you’re feeling, you might recall this instruction: change the way you see it and lean in. Instead of blaming our discomfort on outer circumstances or on our own weakness, we can choose to stay present and awake to our experience, not rejecting it, not grasping it, not buying the stories that we relentlessly tell ourselves. This is priceless advice that addresses the true cause of suffering — yours, mine, and that of all living beings.

Pema Chödron, "Taking the Leap: Freeing Ourselves from Old Habits and Fears"

The Way is perfect like vast space
where nothing is lacking and nothing is in excess.
Indeed, it is due to our choosing to accept or reject
that we do not see the true nature of things.
Be serene in the oneness of things
and such erroneous views will disappear by themselves.

Sengcan (Third Zen Patriarch), Trans. Richard B. Clarke 

Since everything is but an apparition,
Perfect in being what it is,
Having nothing to do with good and bad,
Acceptance or rejection,
You might as well burst out laughing!

Longchenpa, Glimpse After Glimpse: Daily Reflections on Living and Dying"

Caption:
“Be silent and listen: have you recognized your madness and do you admit it? Have you noticed that all your foundations are completely mired in madness? Do you not want to recognize your madness and welcome it in a friendly manner?

You wanted to accept everything. So accept madness too. Let the light of your madness shine, and it will suddenly dawn on you. Madness is not to be despised and not to be feared, but instead you should give it life...If you want to find paths, you should also not spurn madness, since it makes up such a great part of your nature...Be glad that you can recognize it, for you will thus avoid becoming its victim. 

Madness is a special form of the spirit and clings to all teachings and philosophies, but even more to daily life, since life itself is full of craziness and at bottom utterly illogical. Man strives toward reason only so that he can make rules for himself. Life itself has no rules. That is its mystery and its unknown law. What you call knowledge is an attempt to impose something comprehensible on life.”

― Carl Jung

[ Art - “Lanterns” by Varguy ]

Via Lucid Dreams 🙏🏽🤲🏽🥰🥰🥰

Caption:
@socialiststarseed: “Mayor Cherelle Parker’s new communication policy for city agencies, which was quickly reversed for Philadelphia libraries, revealed the severe underfunding and lack of resources given to the city’s 54 branches.

Public libraries serve as safe havens in our communities. In neighborhoods experiencing high rates of gun violence or drug overdose rates, libraries are places that give us anti-violence tools and mental health resources. They are places where we can take a break from the weather, get assistance using online portals to pay bills and go to workshops to discover new interests. Libraries are essential!

Call Mayor Parker to ensure the free flow of information on social services and programming is allowed from all city agencies. In addition, tell the Mayor we need increased funding and expansive resources for our city’s libraries for a safe and healthy city!”

The vision for a life only He can provide, accompanied with the passions to get us there. 

A journey with faith is rarely the easy way out, but it is the most fulfilling…so don’t ever give up 🤍

Caption:
Written by Ken Wilber
Read by Vikas Adam
Format: MP3
Bitrate: 64 Kbps

With practical teachings and detailed instructions, Ken Wilber introduces Integral Mindfulness, a new way of practicing the widely popular meditation. Integral Mindfulness applies many of the leading-edge insights of Ken Wilber’s Integral Theory - the first system to combine Eastern teachings on the five stages of awakening with the eight major Western models of human development, thus portraying the complete path of human evolution. In addition to all the benefits to body, mind, and spirit that standard mindfulness meditation confers, practicing Integral Mindfulness promises a more powerful approach to personal transformation and brings within reach the fullest experience of Enlightenment possible.

Beginning with as little as 15 to 30 minutes of daily sessions, the meditator can gradually expand from there by slowly and easily adding significant aspects of the practice. Meditation instructions and step-by-step guided contemplations are given in detail. Listeners learn how to create a graph to track progress and discover natural strengths and potentials. The book also offers recommended readings and resources to facilitate further study

Caption:
“If I could start again, 

I would install an altar within me. 

I would place the most sacred object inside it: 

my own heart. 

If I could start again, 

I would know that the only cathedral 

I have ever needed to find, to enter, 

to return to again and again, 

is this humble red hermitage, 

this mystical space 

that holds all the answers.

I would begin again inside my heart. 

And I would live this way.

Speaking from it.”

~ Meagan Watterson, Mary Magdalene

Caption:
At a time when there is so much division, isolation and separateness, it’s more important than ever to enhance our emotional connection with others. 

We’re excited to announce that on Sunday 9th June David will be leading a Joyful Heart day retreat at Jamyang Buddhist Centre in London to explore the cultivation of the heart and mind through the practices of the Four Immeasurables. The teachings will be based upon Lama Alan’s book, Four Immeasurables: Practices to Open the Heart.

Explore the transformational practices of the Four Immeasurables - loving-kindness, compassion, empathetic joy and equanimity
Learn techniques that help you connect with others and overcome feelings of isolation.
Engage in meditations that open the heart and promote inner and outer harmony.
Learn how to increase understanding and empathy towards those who challenge us.
Share and learn with like-minded friends in group discussions.

Can’t join in person? You can access the teachings online as well!

Caption:
Lugar de paz en el Camino del Cid

A principios de mayo visité este monasterio donde parece que el tiempo se ha parado. Quizás sea por la tranquila conversación  del monje cisterciense que nos guió en la visita, por el silencio de su iglesia, por la belleza y la paz de su claustro o por  la naturaleza que lo rodea. 

Muy, muy recomendable para los que vivimos en la ciudad y siempre vamos con prisas...

También os dejo algunos apuntes de su historia y su relación con el Cid:

Según el Cantar, el Cid, antes de salir para el destierro, dejó en San Pedro de Cardeña a Jimena y a sus hijas, doña Elvira y doña Sol, encareciendo su cuidado al abad del monasterio. Cuna de muchas leyendas cidianas, fue el lugar donde reposaron durante siglos los restos del Cid y de su esposa Jimena.

El monasterio fue fundado por los benedictinos en 899, constituyéndose en un importante centro cultural y espiritual, especialmente en los primeros momentos de la construcción de Castilla. Del monasterio románico, aún queda la vieja torre del siglo XI y su claustro románico, del siglo XII.

La iglesia es gótica y parte de la fachada es del s. XVIII. Los monjes cistercienses lo ocupan desde 1942 y elaboran vinos y licores de hierbas medicinales.

En 2015, en la aprobación por la Unesco de la ampliación del Camino de Santiago en España a «Caminos de Santiago de Compostela: Camino francés y Caminos del Norte de España», se incluyó el monasterio de San Pedro de Cardeña.

También forma parte de la iniciativa "Camino del Cid" que se puede recorrer siguiendo los pasos del Cid desde Burgos hasta Castellón

Caption:
What if we all loved like this? ⠀
⠀
Tank 🐾 and Daisy 🐾…A perfect depiction of love, only it’s wrapped in fur….What if we looked at each how our fur babies look at us? ⠀
⠀
What if we saw only love when we looked at each other? When we looked at ourself? ⠀
⠀
What if our heart split wide open every time we laid eyes on each other because we only saw the magnificence, brilliance, beauty and light of each other’s Soul, our True self? ⠀
⠀
What if we treated each other the way our fur babies treat us? ⠀
⠀
What if we always thought the best of each other, if we believed we had only the best intentions? ⠀
What if we greeted each other with joy, excitement, a hug, a kiss? ⠀
⠀
What if we took more time to rest, sleep, and play? More time ‘being’ instead of ‘doing’. ⠀
⠀
What if we had the same tolerance, patience and contentment?⠀
⠀
What if we were quick to say I’m sorry, and even quicker to forgive? What if the first person you said that to was yourself? ⠀
⠀
What if you saw yourself the way they see you? What if you loved yourself the way they love you? ⠀
When looking for the perfect representation of love, we don’t need to look any further than our own fur babies. They teach us so much, they are so wise. ⠀
⠀
Their love is not fickle, their love does not fade, it is there day in and day out. A perfect depiction of divine unconditional love…wrapped in fur. ⠀
⠀
This is love. ⠀
⠀
Disassociate love with the negative things that have happened to (for) you, the expectations not being met, and the pain caused by someone you loved. ⠀
⠀
Love does not hurt, it only heals. Hurting people hurt people out of their own unresolved pain. ⠀
⠀
Stop the cycle and feel, open and embrace your own heart, then let love flow and heal. ❤️ I love you. 

xo, Kas 👁️🫶🏼🌈🪽🪄🔮✨

Caption:
Blog: Eine höhere Ebene
Von Karen Berg
Wenn der majestätische Weißkopf-Seeadler aus seinem Platz in den Bergen zu fliegen beginnt, dann scheinen seine Geschwindigkeit und sein Fokus aus einer anderen Welt zu sein. Die Anmut und Schönheit des Adlers werden nur durch seine Präzision und Kraft erreicht. Mit seinen Augen, die sechsmal genauer sehen können als die eines Menschen, ist er in der Lage, sein Ziel mit Geschwindigkeiten von bis zu 160 km/h im Sturzflug zu erreichen. Er scheint wie eine weltfremde Maschinen aus der Zukunft, die Voherrschaft und Stattlichkeit einer anderen Dimension besitzt. Der Adler lehrt uns, wie wichtig Fokussierung, Geschwindigkeit und „Leichtigkeit“ in der Luft sind. Er verkörpert diesen wunderbaren Zustand des Schwebens scheinbar ohne eine Einschränkung durch die Schwerkraft. Der Adler gilt als eines der drei heiligen Naturgeschöpfe. Diese Woche rückt der Sinn und Zweck unseres Lebens (unsere Mission) besonders in den Fokus. [...]

Caption:
I’ve learned that going above and beyond for others who refuse to show up for you leads nowhere good. My time and energy are precious, so I cannot afford to waste them on one-sided relationships anymore, no matter how much history we share or how much I care about the person. 

I used to tolerate lying and cheating, thinking love could conquer all. But the truth is healthy relationships require mutual care, respect, effort, and communication. So now, if trust is broken through deceit or betrayal, I walk away no matter how difficult it is because I deserve faithfulness and honesty, no exceptions, no negotiations. 

Wishy-washy people, hot one day and cold the next, constantly keep you guessing where you stand. I have no place in my life anymore. The emotional rollercoaster is draining and damaging. I should never have to question if someone genuinely wants me in their life regularly. Consistent, committed caring is non-negotiable from here on out.

And if I express clearly that certain behaviors hurt me, but the person refuses to acknowledge responsibility or change, they have to go. Because promises without follow-through mean nothing. I cannot keep making excuses for unremorseful repeat offenses - that’s enabling more mistreatment. I have learned boundaries are the bedrock of healthy relationships. And my inner peace comes first now, above all else.

Caption:
THE THREAD OF DESIRE

What do you desire?  Deeply? Richly? With your whole Being?

Underneath the thinking you know about?  Underneath your invisible thinking? Underneath what you were taught to desire or not desire?  Underneath dogma? Underneath parental conditioning? Underneath cultural conditioning? 
 
When the heart speaks, and you listen with full acceptance and surrender, from the Ground of Being, what do you long for? If the desires are beyond your ego, where do they originate?

I’ve been listening to my heart and its desires with special attention in the past couple of days.  I have done this many times before.  But I have wondered – are the desires of the heart in the afternoon of life different from those of dawn, of morning? 

To read more:

A little ✨Monday fact✨ about me!
I grew up in a catholic household - on my dad’s side. He really wanted me to go in that direction, when it came to religion. But it never really felt right for me, even as a child. Funny how much I’ve changed, now that I believe and trust the universe instead. 
I do still very much respect the religion (and others), and it does give me a Deja-vu-feeling, since every time I enter a church I instantly remember my childhood. 
But one thing I always loved about going to church, was the architecture. I will always love and obsess over it! It is so so beautiful ✨

Caption:
The art of letting go.

I am not faulty or broken. But for far too long, I have worn masks that don't belong to me. I've carried insecurities, old memories, pain, resentment, and mean inner voices that someone people planted in me. Until one day, I learned the art of letting go. By examining every part of my life where unpleasant things had happened, I realized they were just unpleasant stories and experiences meant to teach me. Why did I hold onto them for so long? Who knows? Somehow, I thought avoiding those feelings would protect me. But feeling them all finally freed me. We are not our stories. They are just stories that pass by, and we are the ones who should let them go.Beneeth all that, there is truth. And that truth is - your soul. 

From heart,
Esor Venus

Caption:
Cara melakukan “Nivritti” atau penarikan diri dalam spiritualitas Hindu, bisa cukup bervariasi tergantung dari pada preferensi individual serta tradisi spiritual yang diikuti. Namun, ada beberapa prinsip umum yang bisa membimbing praktik tersebut:

1. Meditasi dan Refleksi: Luangkan waktu untuk bermeditasi setiap hari. Dengan bermeditasi, kita bisa menenangkan pikiran, meningkatkan kesadaran, serta memperdalam pemahaman spiritual.
2. Pengendalian Indriya (Pancaindriya): Latih pengendalian diri atas panca indriya, atau lima indra (panca indriya) – penglihatan, pendengaran, penciuman, perasa, dan perasaan. Hindari rangsangan yang bisa mengganggu konsentrasi spiritual.
3. Pemujaan dan Pengabdian: Lakukan pemujaan, maupun pengabdian kepada Tuhan atau Dewa-Dewi, sesuai dengan keyakinan spiritual. Ini bisa melibatkan menyanyikan, kirtan, bhajan (lagu devosional), membaca sastra suci, atau melakukan puja (upacara pemujaan).
4.  Latihan Yoga: Latihan yoga secara teratur, juga bisa membantu dalam memperkuat tubuh, mengontrol pernapasan, serta meningkatkan keseimbangan fisik dan mental.
5. Sangha atau Komunitas Spiritual: Temukan komunitas spiritual, atau guru yang mampu membimbing serta mendukung, dalam perjalanan spiritual. Diskusikan pengalaman, dan belajar dari yang lain melalui komunitas tersebut.
6. Renungan dan Introspeksi: Lakukan refleksi diri secara teratur, untuk mengevaluasi nilai-nilai, kebiasaan, serta motivasi. Renungkan tentang tujuan spiritual, juga langkah-langkah yang bisa diambil untuk mendekatinya.
7. Menjalani Hidup Sederhana: Kurangi keterikatan pada benda materi, serta gaya hidup duniawi yang berlebihan. Praktikkan kesederhanaan, dan belajar untuk hidup dengan penuh kesadaran, juga kebijaksanaan.
8. Pendidikan dan Pembelajaran: Teruslah belajar, serta berkembang secara spiritual. Baca sastra suci, teliti ajaran-ajaran spiritual, juga mencari inspirasi dari guru-guru spiritual yang bijaksana.

Caption:
▪️sobre sentidos

Nem sempre escutamos quando ouvimos. Seja o som do entorno, uma voz alheia, ou a nossa própria.

Hoje,  n' "O Livro dos Chacras" de Osho, prendeu-me uma secção que se dedicava a falar sobre a forma como usamos os nossos sentidos. Dizia que não é por sermos capaz de ver, ouvir ou sentir, que Vemos, Ouvimos ou Sentimos. Que há diferentes níveis de dedicação na forma como recebemos as informações. Que Sentir é (ou pode ser) muito mais do que experimentar o mundo através dos órgãos de percepção. Podemos ser realmente atravessados pelo que nos chega; vibrar e fundir-nos com qualquer objeto da nossa apreciação, seja qual for o nosso meio de interação com ele. É como ir da superfície às profundezas da experiência.

Já experimentaram ou experimentam esta abertura às coisas do mundo? Se sim, quando?

Eu, também, tento conservar essa dedicação ao instante. E é verdade que o banal deixa de existir.

Assim disse Meister Eckhart:

"Estes olhos pertencem ao divino.
Ele viu-se a si próprio através de mim."

Caption:
Today lets talk about the moon as a symbol.

the moon is the second of all the symbols, and it stands for transformation, rebirth, and the passing of time.

The moon is the symbol of a never-ending cycle of change. 

the moon reminds us that time is ever moving forward, It moves from stage to stage, and so do we. 

As we move through life, we move on from certain parts unto new horizons.
we grow and we learn. 

I hope the moon can help you move on to your next stage in life.

Tomorrow I will be talking about the next symbol: the star.

please follow me if you enjoy these small explanations and like to see more.

Caption:
Last weekend, I opened up a conversation about grief in my stories. A few beautiful and open conversations unfolded.

Thank you; you know who you are🫶🏻

It made me reflect on some lessons learned along the way, although there is much more to share about this topic.

Of course, grief can come in many forms and shapes: the loss of a loved one, a pet, even a job, place, or an old version version of yourself.

You might even be grieving someone who is still alive.

Sending love to anyone who might need it♥️

Know that you are not alone and your emotions are valid.

Love,
Femke Valerie

My happy place 🥰

It is a honor to share the gift of somatic breathwork. I’m always so humbled and amazed when I witness the transformations that happen in each journey 🫶🏼

Talk therapy alone sometimes isn’t enough to clear the emotional baggage you carry from trauma and stress. Deep work happens when you begin to incorporate somatic practices in your wellness toolbox.

Identify your passion, determine how to incorporate it into a purpose, and always persevere. \n\nDelve further into the art of living, with our deck of 52 enCOURAGEment cards to lead the way. Inspiration to guide you through work and play.

Thought of the Day - June 3rd, 2024

Caption:
Such a powerful healing hike yesterday at Wahclella Falls with some amazing beautiful souls. Thank you for such depth and vulnerability in your shares and prayers. 

We walked in silence, listening and seeing natures abundance all around us. Feeling our understanding of the language of Mother Earth. We reflected and shared our insights with each other alongside our beautiful plant medicine of Cacao. Her heart opening and strength allows us to look deeper within and share our truth. 

We sent our prayers to the water and offered apart of our hearts for the ones we love. Sending more gratitude and appreciation for the abundant clean water we get to bath in. We don’t have to be scared of a little rain…we can celebrate the gifts of clearing and cleansing it offers us. 

Thank you Mother Nature 🙏💚 and those who took time out of their weekend to walk along side me

Caption:
♡ Unknown Facts about Ayurvdeva ♡

1 Oil Pulling for Detox: Did you know oil pulling is an Ayurvedic practice? Swishing with coconut oil can help detoxify your mouth and improve oral health.

2  Daily Tongue Scraping: Ever wonder about tongue scraping? It's an Ayurvedic practice that removes toxins and improves taste! Try it every morning for a fresher start.

3  Sleep is a Dosha: Feeling sluggish? Your sleep dosha might be imbalanced! Ayurveda emphasizes sleep hygiene for optimal energy.

4  Spice Up Your Life: Spices aren't just for flavor! Ayurveda uses spices like ginger and turmeric to balance your doshas and promote digestion. #SpiceUpYourLife

5  Listen to Your Body's Clock: Ayurveda teaches us to listen to our body's natural rhythm. Early dinners and waking with the sunrise can boost energy.

Wer böse sein möchte, hat es sehr einfach. Er muss nur vernichten, was andere schön finden. Das reicht oftmals schon.
Denn warum sollte ich vernichten, was nicht schlecht ist, was andere gut finden, was mir selbst nichts weiter bedeutet? 
Seid nicht destruktiv gegen die anderen und lasst ihnen ihre Güte, wo sie euch gegenüber nicht böse ist.
Die Welt ist besser, wenn wir einander gewähren lassen und die Schönheit genießen, die wir einander spenden können.

Caption: In this episode of Vision Chat we get to know Yesenia Maldonado, licensed clinical social worker, entrepreneur and social justice ambassador. Yesenia takes us on a journey of overcoming life obstacles, struggles and the beautiful gifts of healing and joy she has found along the way. Yesenia’s passion for her city, culture and helping people, shine through as she shares with us the lessons she has learned in life and the keys to healthy, happy living. Yesenia believes in healing through play and tells us about the 200 games she has collected over the years and ultimately opening up a board game cafe with her husband of 26 years.  Yesenia has done it all! Social worker, clinical supervisor, executive director, adjunct professor, hurricane recovery volunteer, entrepreneur, certified trauma informed yoga instructor and consultant. It was such a joy to get to talk with this incredibly wise, resilient, powerful woman, we hope you enjoy it as much as we did. Oh, and if you are in Chicago, stop into her cafe and challenge her to a round of UNO! Caption:
The Mamos are the teachers of wisdom and keepers of the knowledge of the Kogi. They are the elders. In order to become a Mamo, very early on in their life, they spend 18 years in darkness in a cave.

Mama Bernardo, almost 100 years old, recalls his time as a young child in the cave: 
"I was very very young, I can't remember exactly, when the Mamos took me to the cave. I had just been born. I grew up in the cave. I thought I was the only person in the world. Sometimes the Mamos came to visit me, then I thought that there was only us, me and the other Mamos. When I was a bit older, the Mamos took me to their house, but it was always dark. During the day I never went outside. I didn't know I had a father, I didn't know I had a mother. The only thing I was concerned with all the time was energy. I learned how to sing to the water, I learned how to sing to the trees.

It was always very, very dark. I never saw anyone, but sometimes I heard the Mamos speak to me from afar. There I learned everything.

Why are we being taught in the cave? Why are we being initiated in the dark? The reason is that it is very dark in the cave, and in the darkness are the fathers and mothers of all things. Everything that is alive; the trees, the water, the lakes, the stones, has thoughts, which are their fathers and mothers, and they live in the darkness. And this is where one learns to speak with them."

Caption:
They might let you believe that they do… but the truth is nobody knows what they are doing.

We strongly want to believe that at least the ruling people in countries or CEOs of big companies knows a thing or two. But honestly, sometimes it feels a lot like  we are all players in this game and it’s a bit like “make the best player win”.

I’m all about transparency and authenticity, but if you need to fake it till you make it for your own sake. For making it out the door, out of the spiritual closet or to start speaking your truth. Permission officially granted. OK? If you were waiting for a moment this is it.
